com.xtructure.xneat.evolution
Interface NEATSurvivalFilter

All Superinterfaces:
EvolutionObject, SurvivalFilter
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractNEATSurvivalFilter, NEATSurvivalFilterImpl
public interface NEATSurvivalFilter
extends SurvivalFilter

The NEATSurvivalFilter interface describes the methods for marking dead NEATGenomes and species in a population. Classes implementing this interface should mark NEATGenomes for death, essentially selecting which genomes will survive into the next generation.

NEATSurvivalFilter instances should not remove genomes or species, leaving them for removal at the discretion of the NEATEvolutionStrategy.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
